<br>
I was curious as to what each class/race combo has seen for a health gain each level. I made my warrior as my first character over a year and a half ago and before I understood the game. I've never regretted by-passing the common trend of making an ogre or troll just because they are the 'ideal' race for tanking, or at least considered to be by people that don't play a warrior. The majority of warriors I think will agree it doesn't matter so much for ability, but they do have an edge in the health department. Currently my warrior stands at 2207 health naked with 4 levels left to go. Sooo, if no huge increase, I'm going to settle at about 2350 health at level 60.<br>
<br>
I'm sure everyone would like more health, but I really don't see anything wrong with throwing the warrior 10 or so more each level to keep a nice lead in the defense department (like giving better defenses to hybrids will change it much) hehe.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uwindailya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Windailya</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 3:27:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> Well, i have a 55 wood elf warrior, and my health when naked is at like 2180 i believe, not totally sure though, trolls and ogres absolutely own us in the HP department :) but thats okay cus we make being a warrior, look good :D<br>
<br>
but yea now i'm curious on what other race/class combos get as far as hp's go per level <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uipstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IPStar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 3:49:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> Hrmm, I forgot.  But Gell, my 57 Paladin has around 2220 hp unbuffed, and im guessing that puts him at around 18-1900 naked?  I'm not really sure i'll check it when i log in again, since I die 3-4 times a night. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugreycloud69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greycloud69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 6:09:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> You are at a disadvantage being a DE, but do not give up hope. Try to gather as much +stamina and +hp gear as you can that also does not make you lose too much AC at the same time.<br>
<br>
You will get nice HP jumps at 59 and 60 if I remember correctly, but nothing to make up for the 27 and 30 hp gains you make at the early 50s. Unbuffed I sit at 1100 AC with 3600 HP, but I wear almost all stamina and HP gear as a barbarian. If you want to get some ideas for items you might need email me at Greycloud@afterlifeguild.org and I will be glad to give you some help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzzod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zzod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 6:26:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> I remember reading something a while back that said the higher your stamina is the MORE hp you gain every time you level. Well if that is true, I would wear all stamina gear until I hit 60 to gain as much hp as possible and then when you hit 60 balance it out for proper AC STR and STA gear.../shrug <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ugreycloud69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greycloud69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 6:52:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> Heh, I am sure that it would be on base stamina not current. Otherwise people would just get a STA buff before they dinged. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ujpnrgizer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JPnrgizer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 7:31:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> It is my opinion that whatever sta you have at any one point in time determines your hp by level.  ie.  If you have 150 sta points when you ding and have 2200 hp, it would not make a difference if you upped your sta to 170 before you dinged.  When you had 150 sta at any point during that level you would have you would have the hp that you would have had if you had dinged with 150 sta (being 2200).  When you were naked, you would have whatever hp your base sta requires.  I have no proof of this, it is just my opinion =)<br>
<br>
<br>
There is, however, a difference between BASE stats and MODIFIED stats.  If a person had 130 sta base and another had 120 base but had 10 points of modifiers, the person with 130 base with no modifiers would have MORE hp at the same sta in the same level.  I have seen allot of documentation of this for all stats in many places and thouroghly believe it to be true. =)<br>
<br>
Nrgizer Hase<br>
Cavalier of North Freeport<br>
Chaotic Faith<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uthoggdlogg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThoggDlogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg!</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 10:44:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> HEH</span><hr size=1> Wars gain hp at a flat rate from sta increases aprox just shy of 6 hp per sta.<br>
<br>
havieng 150 base sta vs 140 will mean 60 hp at level 60<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueuthanasiawarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euth Anasia Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 12:01:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> hehe when ya raise a level, the ONLY thing that determines how many HP's you get is your BASE staimina.  Jewelry/Eqipment etc is not taken into account for when you level.  I know a guy on Nameless (where I have a 60 mage) who is a Ogre Warrior that put all his starting points in Stamina and a 60 Ogre warrior that put all his point in Dex/Str.  The one with more base Stamina has around 250 more HP at level 60 than the other Ogre if i remember correctly....Which may not seem like much, but it really is a big factor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uxilithtvyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xilith Tvyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.neriak.com/rune4.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Innoruuk's personal bodyguard</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#993300>(2/14/01 12:30:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Health gain per level?</span><hr size=1> I believe the hp from stamina contribution follows this Formula:<br>
<br>
Hp/Stamina = Level/50 * C<br>
<br>
Where C is a class dependent value.<br>
<br>
For hybrids it is 4.<br>
For Warriors it is 5.<br>
<br>
So at level 56 I get 4.48 hp / stamina, which I think is about right.<br>
<br>
That yields 6 hp / stamina for a level 60 warrior.<br>
<br>
Though at some levels you get a larger bonus, which throws it off a tad. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showMessage?topicID=1198.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showMessage?topicID=1264.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.threadControl?topicID=1262.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1262.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1262.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub28.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="drinal28133frm1">General<option value="drinal28133frm2">Trading<option value="drinal28133frm9">Quests<option value="drinal28133frm10">Screenshots<option value="drinal28133frm11">Role-playing<option value="drinal28133frm12">Flames<option value="drinal28133frm17">Guild Information<option value="drinal28133frm4">Hate Raids<option value="drinal28133frm5">Fear Raids<option value="drinal28133frm6">Sky Raids<option value="drinal28133frm21">Growth Raids<option value="drinal28133frm22">Mischief Raids<option value="drinal28133frm20">Dragon Raids<option value="drinal28133frm16">Suggestions - Forums & Webpage<option value="drinal28133frm23">Epi